The paper discusses the use of reinforcement learning to validate the results of empirical game-theoretic analysis in a continuous double auction market. This involves analyzing the behavior of multiple agents in a complex strategic environment, which falls under the categories of artificial intelligence (cs.AI), game theory (cs.GT), machine learning (cs.LG), multiagent systems (cs.MA), and control systems (cs.SY).
